body_html: When you run decoding, you basically have to have the same parameters as when you trained. For example, you forgot to add --size=64 to the second command, and the number 64 is one of the incompatible dimensions. I bet if you look at the code, you'll see that the default value for size is 1024.

body: When you run decoding, you basically have to have the same parameters as when you trained.  For example, you forgot to add --size=64 to the second command, and the number 64 is one of the incompatible dimensions.  I bet if you look at the code, you'll see that the default value for size is 1024.
